@noahp6886 The problem is that this was supposed to be a group discussion, but Malcolm not only dominated the speaking time, he used that time largely to be dismissive of any POVs that disagreed with, effectively shutting half of the participants out. 

On top of that, he started the discussion by insisting on speaking first, at which point he insisted he wasn't really going to participate, then attempted to self-righteously shut the whole thing down before anyone else had a chance to even enter the conversation, let alone offer a differing perspective or opinion. "Foreign Man," opened up with a very relevant & productive set of comments, then pretty much never spoke again, while Malcolm repeatedly pulled focus.

Cam Newton might need to sit with shame for a while; I think Malcolm may need to sit with humility.
